ANNOUCEMENT: WE SOLD OUR COFFEE SHOP!!!

Just wanna first say mahalos to all my friends old and new for the support! We couldn’t have done it without you 🫶

I know I have been teasing this for a while but I needed to take the time to let my emotion and thoughts align.

 I have so much coming up down the pipeline with relaunching @Kirralife, traveling, & on all work projects that I needed to be smart with my time and respect my value. That being said, my partners at Little lunch and I had different visions. 

Jerrod & I the original founders have truly put our heart and soul into bringing little lunch to life. We brought in the other partners, I saved up money working as a model which was initially for our wedding. Instead, we invested into starting the shop in the middle of a pandemic. @Jerrodclancy literally built it with his bare hands & we dreamt up the australian coffee shop concept with jerrods childhood in mind-Little Lunch: meaning recess in australia. I executed our conceptualizing, brought my friends in to be apart of it, & birthed the infamous the coco cold brew to venice. Jerrod and I were so specific to the taste of the coffee & the brands we wanted there. This was a place where we laughed and to be completely honest cried a lot. 

When I knew it was time to conserve my energy to relaunch our first baby @kirralife, I definitely had a hard time letting the soul of the cafe leave with us. However, my dad said something that truly stuck with me “an artist may sell his masterpiece but that artist has 20 more sitting at home waiting to be seen.” 

I think this has been a HUGE self reflection for me as well because I battle with not feeling deserving of claiming the successes big or small that Jerrod and I have built. To me I am my biggest believer and my worst enemy. Until the things I build hit the standard of success that I set for it, it’s hard to acknowledge the little wins. 

I want to remember to stop and take some of the small wins. I can not wait to share with you the relaunch of @Kirralife. It’s everything we have been dreaming up and working towards over the past 2 years!!!! Thank you for all your support, to my old & new friends. Stay tuned!

I have SO much I could say about the condo I bought in 2021. TBH I can’t really sum this up in a reel. If you wanna get a little more nosey I have a highlight on my page of reno clips. 

There is a couple reasons this has taken me forever to share:
1. We did our own reno and lived from room to room. By the time the 8 month reno was mostly finished I didn’t want to think about it for another second let alone make more content on it. I just wanted to live like a normal person. We were confined to eating, sleeping, and working in one room and the rest of the condo was in dust and rubble. 
2. When you own you are never really “finished”. I was so focused on it being “done” to feel confident sharing. But in reality we only just got the AC installed, we had to redo the second bathroom ceiling 3 times, and the master shower twice. So ya it’s never really “done”. 
3. A lot of the furniture I had was kind of just to get us by since we had been dumping money into the remodel. I only just got furniture that is a bit of me a few months ago. 

The original condo looked NOTHING like this. Even the before & afters couldn’t do justice to the problem solving @jerrodclancy and I did. We had 15 different scenarios of how to lay out the kitchen with all different price points. We had to make the condo functional; for example the original galley style kitchen drawers and cabinets would open into each other and the kitchen was closed off by a wall in the middle of the living room. There was no closet space, storage, or lighting. We not only did cosmetic updates but reconfigured walls. 

After seeing how much waste & toxic materials were used I really wanted to make the house as non toxic as possible going forward. From cleaning supplies to products! 

Honestly this was one of our biggest projects jerrod and I did which followed right after we started and built the coffee shop & were in the midst of working on relaunching @kirralife 

A reel just can’t get into the granular details, maybe a longer format like YouTube could be a fun way to get into it? Let me know if there’s any interest!
